    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I’ve always enjoyed sites that had easter eggs in their consoles, whether they’re simple and whimsical like Ponyfoo.com</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 570px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bc30390af4e06b9340a4f34c5e77c434/e8950/ponyfoo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 69.23076923076923%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Ponyfoo has a &quot;welcome adventurer&quot; message in their console\"\n        title=\"Ponyfoo has a &quot;welcome adventurer&quot; message in their console\"\n        src=\"/static/bc30390af4e06b9340a4f34c5e77c434/432e7/ponyfoo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bc30390af4e06b9340a4f34c5e77c434/a6b04/ponyfoo.png 143w,\n/static/bc30390af4e06b9340a4f34c5e77c434/0e2fe/ponyfoo.png 285w,\n/static/bc30390af4e06b9340a4f34c5e77c434/432e7/ponyfoo.png 570w,\n/static/bc30390af4e06b9340a4f34c5e77c434/77800/ponyfoo.png 855w,\n/static/bc30390af4e06b9340a4f34c5e77c434/b5cea/ponyfoo.png 1140w,\n/static/bc30390af4e06b9340a4f34c5e77c434/e8950/ponyfoo.png 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>or practical like Facebook’s</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 570px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/18f8473330556eccf15a6bf869f37e5a/f349c/facebook.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 60.83916083916083%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Facebook warns people about scams in the console\"\n        title=\"Facebook warns people about scams in the console\"\n        src=\"/static/18f8473330556eccf15a6bf869f37e5a/432e7/facebook.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/18f8473330556eccf15a6bf869f37e5a/a6b04/facebook.png 143w,\n/static/18f8473330556eccf15a6bf869f37e5a/0e2fe/facebook.png 285w,\n/static/18f8473330556eccf15a6bf869f37e5a/432e7/facebook.png 570w,\n/static/18f8473330556eccf15a6bf869f37e5a/77800/facebook.png 855w,\n/static/18f8473330556eccf15a6bf869f37e5a/b5cea/facebook.png 1140w,\n/static/18f8473330556eccf15a6bf869f37e5a/f349c/facebook.png 2002w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I’m also part of a <a href=\"https://www.kustomer.com/\">fast growing company</a> and we’re always hiring, so I thought I’d see if I could leave a fun message in the console, and play around with ASCII art while I was at it.</p>\n<p>Kustomer’s logo is <em>Kusty</em>; a smily speech bubble with apostrophes for eyes:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 570px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/80799b63db397c007bcc85e9d9bc4c17/2bef9/logo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.34965034965035%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Kustomer logo\"\n        title=\"Kustomer logo\"\n        src=\"/static/80799b63db397c007bcc85e9d9bc4c17/432e7/logo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/80799b63db397c007bcc85e9d9bc4c17/a6b04/logo.png 143w,\n/static/80799b63db397c007bcc85e9d9bc4c17/0e2fe/logo.png 285w,\n/static/80799b63db397c007bcc85e9d9bc4c17/432e7/logo.png 570w,\n/static/80799b63db397c007bcc85e9d9bc4c17/77800/logo.png 855w,\n/static/80799b63db397c007bcc85e9d9bc4c17/2bef9/logo.png 1024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>So how did I get Kusty showing up in the console on this site?  I started with a bit of a cheat: I asciified the logo using <a href=\"https://www.asciify.me/\">asciify.me/</a>.  That got me a nice starting place, I had an Ascii version of Kusty to work with:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\"> ' ``.'` . -_+\")cTtfyyyszztszszszztzfztfsfzsfzsstttyt17vr>, .   ` '-`- `\n  ..`.'`.~)71tyyzzfzfzsyststztyftsytsystyztzzyzsyyytyfsytf1l?!  -.` `'`.\n-.- - `+}Tzztsfyffztzzyyztsffyytfyyzztyfzyfzyfystzftszfytfysyt{+--'.- `.\n `--.>Lyffttyztsfyztyt11fYtyyzYTz1yT1yfzfTt1TsYfftsttzzysffssyyt7+  ''`-\n -`!iysttfstffzTi?\"+,,!~^~!^__~!_:,:^^^,!~_~~:_,,!:^+/i1zyytfyztzzi~''-.\n. !}tsftzffyTv+~..  -`-.' '. .`-   .'.-- ` ` . -'- .-..~+v1fsfttszf}&lt; . \n ,xftyyysszv, -. ```' '. .-.``'.-   ''.'--'- '  ` ...''  .!vytyzsstsx^- \n'/zsstzzzf*` `` '  ` `- 